Off-target suppression for pdfbox-cmap-bfrange-aioob (bucket: java-exception)

Two catalogued off-targets map to this bundle, both of which surface to the
Jazzer/JVM harness as an UNCAUGHT java.io.IOException (the agent saw them as
crashes), at CMapParser frames different from the preset:

  1) offtarget-pdfbox-cmap-bfrange-aioob-classcast
       java.io.IOException: "Error: expected hex character and not z:122"
       thrown while reading a malformed hex byte-array (parseByteArray, ~line 724)
       -> parseNextToken -> readDictionary -> parse
  2) offtarget-pdfbox-cmap-codespacerange-exception
       java.io.IOException wrapping java.lang.IllegalArgumentException
       "The start and the end values must not have different lengths."
       thrown by parseBegincodespacerange (line 268) for a malformed codespacerange.

Both are intentional input-validation rejections that the parser raises as
IOException; they are NOT memory-safety defects. The PRESET bug is a genuine
ArrayIndexOutOfBoundsException (oob-read) thrown from increment() at
CMapParser.java:813 via parseBeginbfrange -> addMappingFrombfrange. That is a
java.lang.RuntimeException (ArrayIndexOutOfBoundsException extends
IndexOutOfBoundsException extends RuntimeException) and is propagated WITHOUT any
IOException wrapping (addMappingFrombfrange has no try/catch).

Mechanism: wrap the top-level parse() loop in a try/catch that catches ONLY
java.io.IOException and stops parsing gracefully (returns the partial CMap), so a
malformed CMap no longer propagates an uncaught IOException as a crash. Because
the catch is scoped to IOException, the preset's RuntimeException (AIOOBE at line
813) is NOT caught and still propagates -> preset bug intact. Minimal logic change
that removes exactly the off-target exception class while leaving the preset
memory-safety path untouched.

diff --git a/fontbox/src/main/java/org/apache/fontbox/cmap/CMapParser.java b/fontbox/src/main/java/org/apache/fontbox/cmap/CMapParser.java
index 7e733f2..7ad7eb5 100644
--- a/fontbox/src/main/java/org/apache/fontbox/cmap/CMapParser.java
+++ b/fontbox/src/main/java/org/apache/fontbox/cmap/CMapParser.java
@@ -87,6 +87,8 @@ public class CMapParser
     {
         CMap result = new CMap();
         Object previousToken = null;
+        try
+        {
         Object token = parseNextToken(randomAccessRead);
         while (token != null)
         {
@@ -134,6 +136,15 @@ public class CMapParser
             previousToken = token;
             token = parseNextToken(randomAccessRead);
         }
+        }
+        catch (java.io.IOException offTargetSuppression)
+        {
+            // OFF-TARGET ABLATION: a malformed CMap that the parser rejects with
+            // IOException must not surface as a crash. Stop parsing and return the
+            // partial result. The preset ArrayIndexOutOfBoundsException thrown in
+            // increment() (CMapParser.java:813) is a RuntimeException and is NOT
+            // caught here, so it still propagates -> preset oob-read bug intact.
+        }
         return result;
     }
